### ============================================
### Exports (Phase 9)
### ============================================

### Get Available Export Formats
GET {{baseUrl}}/exports/formats

###

### Create Export Bundle
### First create a model and get results, then use result IDs here
# @name createExport
POST {{baseUrl}}/exports
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "modelId": "{{modelId}}",
  "modelName": "Export Test Model",
  "items": [
    { "resultId": "result-1" }
  ]
}

###

### Get Export ID from response
@exportId = {{createExport.response.body.exportId}}

### Download Export as ZIP
### Note: This returns binary data - best tested in browser
GET {{baseUrl}}/exports/{{exportId}}/download

###

### Create Shareable Link
# @name createShareLink
POST {{baseUrl}}/exports/{{exportId}}/share
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "expiresInHours": 24,
  "maxDownloads": 10
}

###

### Get Share Token from response
@shareToken = {{createShareLink.response.body.token}}

### Download via Share Link (public URL)
### Note: This returns binary data - best tested in browser
GET {{baseUrl}}/share/{{shareToken}}

###

### Export Error Cases
### ============================================

### Export with non-existent bundle (404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/exports/does-not-exist/download

###

### Share non-existent export (404)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exports/does-not-exist/share
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "expiresInHours": 24
}

###

### Invalid share token (404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/share/invalid-token

###

### Create export with missing modelId (400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exports
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "items": [{ "resultId": "test" }]
}

###

### Create export with empty items (400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exports
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "modelId": "test-model",
  "modelName": "Test",
  "items": []
}
